          "Title": "Property Tax",
          "UserDescription": "For each individual plot in Going Merry a property tax must be paid.\nThe purpose of this tax is to fund infrastructure (roads) as well as city projects, both cultural (museum, school) and administrative (town hall, warehouse & harbor, silo trade).\n\n<b>Regular Citizen:</b> This amounts to €2 per day per claimed plot excluding the starting 16 homestead claims.\r\n<b>Company Citizens:</b> This amounts to €2 per day per claimed plot excluding 16 homestead claims multiplied with the count of employees of the company. (there is a little flaw in the calculation, observe and revise!)\n\r\nThe property tax remains at the same level over all time and balances out the lower purchasing cost of Town Claim Papers and Town Claim Stakes.",
